casebody.data:
Wednesday, November 8, 1995

DISCRETIONARY APPEALS ALLOWED

95-650. Kulch v. Structural Fibers, Inc.

Geauga County, No. 93-G-1824. On motion to dissolve/lift stay and on motion to strike. Motion to dissolve/lift stay granted; sua sponte, discretionary appeal allowed.

Moyer, C.J., and Cook, J., dissent. Wright, J., would hold this cause for the decision in 95-100, Trader v. People Working Cooperatively, Inc., Hamilton County, No. C-930716.
